rComments: Wow, where to begin. The machine learning course was whirlwind of knowledge that kept me at the edge of my seat. From the first slide to the last I was captivated. Was not expecting the pop quiz at the end, so I did horribly. But his encouragement kept me motivated, I have already signed up for his next course.
The machine learning sessions are super useful, the quizzes are very clear, but watch out for the last question!

Professor Keng is a fair professor. Be ready to work hard taking his classes, but it'll pay off with a good handle of the course material, fair testing and assignments (which should translate to somewhat decent grades), and the occasional classroom snack session.

This course is one of the best I have taken so far. I am a big fan of CLRS, and Prof. Keng does a great job at motivating you to go through this big book in a semester. I also find him quite inspiring because of his industry background.
Professor Keng is hard but very fair, he jokes often, but his jokes does not contain a hint of racism.
